comments: White (CHI) dives to the floor and makes contact with Dort's (OKC) head as he attempts to secure the ball.
Williams (OKC) briefly grasps Vucevic's (CHI) arm and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
LaVine (CHI) is bracing for the contact from Williams (OKC) and releases away from the contact.
Giddey (OKC) brings his arm down and makes contact with LaVine's (CHI) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Jerome (OKC) clamps and holds Green's (CHI) right arm and restricts his ability to retrieve the rebound.
White (CHI) is retreating alongside GIlgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
LaVine's (CHI) brushes Jerome's (OKC) arm and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) contests Jerome's (OKC) driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs after the release of the shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) legally contests Vucevic's (CHI) jump shot attempt.  The marginal lower body contact is caused by Vucevic after he has released his jump shot.
White (CHI) is moving alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Brown Jr. (CHI) legally contests Dort's (OKC) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Jerome (OKC) brings his hand forward towards LaVine's (CHI) front and marginal contact occurs as LaVIne gathers the ball.
Williams (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he could be deemed to be imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Brown Jr. (CHI) and Giddey (OKC) briefly engage and disengage as they attempt to secure the rebound.
Dort (OKC) maintains a legal pivot foot as he begins his dribble.
White (CHI) is moving alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
LaVine (CHI) applies a stayed left hand to Giddey's (OKC) back and the contact is marginal.
Jerome (OKC) commits a take foul on LaVine (CHI).
Vucevic (CHI) and Dort (OKC) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Dort (OKC) turns into LaVine's (CHI) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
LaVine (CHI) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Dort (OKC) makes contact with Green's (CHI) head after he has secured the rebound.
